Retired Anglican bishop Njongonkulu Ndungane says Archbishop Desmond Tutu is in good spirits and is well on the road to recovery. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Retired Anglican bishop Njongonkulu Ndungane says Archbishop Desmond Tutu is in good spirits and is well on the road to recovery. READ: Tutu hospitalised for 'stubborn' infection Ndungane says Tutu's surgery, following an infection, went well. Tutu has been hospitalised several times over the past few years for the treatment of a similar condition.